# Ultra Low Power RISC-V with ESP-IDF

Ultra Low Power (ULP) RISC-V examples and applications for ESP32 microcontrollers using the ESP-IDF framework. This project focuses on ultra-low-energy embedded systems, autonomous background processing, sensor monitoring, wake-up control, and optimized power consumption techniques.

## Features
* ULP RISC-V programming with ESP-IDF
* Deep sleep and wake-up management
* Autonomous sensor monitoring
* GPIO control from ULP core
* Low-power optimization techniques
* Example applications for ESP32 series
* Modular and easy-to-expand structure

## Supported Devices
* ESP32-S2
* ESP32-S3
* ESP32-C3
* ESP32-C6
* ESP32-H2

## Requirements
* ESP-IDF v5.x or newer
* Python 3
* CMake
* Ninja build system

## Installation

Clone the repository:

    git clone https://github.com/your-user/ultra-low-power-riscv-esp-idf.git
    cd ultra-low-power-riscv-esp-idf

Export ESP-IDF environment:

    source $HOME/esp/esp-idf/export.sh

Build the project:

    idf.py build

Flash to the board:

    idf.py -p /dev/ttyUSB0 flash monitor

